# Background
- Silicon wafers are typically doped to either be a 
   p-type wafer or a n-type wafer
- In CMOS IC processing the wafer is typically doped
    to be p-type
- When the wafer is p-type, NMOS are fabricated directly 
   in the p-type wafer 
   - And the PMOS, are fabricated in an n-well
      - referred to as the bulk/body of the MOSFET
	- Most processes use an *n-well process* 
	  - So a p-type substrate with n-well
