# The Well
- The Well is the first layer fabricated when making CMOS ICs 
- When using the n-well in a p-substrate the two form a diode 
   - This is okay because the substrate is usually tied to ground/lowest voltage in the circuit
      - This is to stop the diode from forward biasing
+ The n-well can also be used as a resistor 
