## Patterning 
- We build together CMOS circuits by patterning different layers on and in the wafer 
  - We start off with the bare wafer (p-type or n-type)
   - We then grow an oxide layer(glass or $SiO_2$)
     - And on top of that we add our Photo-resist Oxide layer
- Lastly our mask is placed in front of a UV light to 
leaving us with our exposed photo resist
- We then etch the oxide layer to expose the wafer
- We then remove the remaining photo resist
