#### Wet Oxide
- A Wet oxide is is created using $H_{2}O$
+ Wet Oxides main benefit is the fast growing time
+ Its drawback is the hydrogen byproduct
 + And its not as pure as the dry oxide

##### Both
+ Both are known as thermal oxides due to the increased temp used during oxide growth
+ The growth rate increases with temperature
+ Any type of oxide growth in this process consumes silicon
   - This overall thickness of the oxide is related to the thickness of the consumed silicon 
       - Which is given by
     $x_{si} = 0.45 \cdot x_{ox}$
