#### Dry Oxide
- A Dry Oxide is created using $O_{2}$
+ Dry Oxide takes a much longer time to grow 
### Photoresist
- To sum it up there are two types of photo resist 
  - Positive resist which allows us to use a mask to remove illuminated areas 
     - Negative resist which allows us to use a mask to remove areas that were not exposed to light
- Using both types of resist allows the process designer 
to cut down on the number of masks needed to define a pattern
### N-well Creation
- N-well creation starts by diffusing donor atoms
  - those with five valence electrons (four in silicon)
- The process starts by depositing a layer of resist(without oxide) directly onto the wafer
- We then expose the resist to light through a mask to remove it 
- We then expose the wafer to donor atoms 
   - the resist blocks the diffusion in areas we don't want diffusion to occur in 
- The areas that are exposed start to create an n-well
  - We control the depth of the n-well by increasing the time under diffusion
- Lastly the resist is finally removed 
  #### Note
  - The final n-well size is not the same as the mask size
   - Foundry's may bloat or shrink the mask to compensate for lateral diffusion

